##Wuhan "Alumni Association" of ten medical students

Wechat, bingdianweekly

Features, China Youth Daily's in depth reporting brand. We believe that news has more than one day of life.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
At 2:00 am on February 29, Zheng Xuwang, a nurse in the ICU isolation ward of Wuhan First Hospital, was filling out a report form of adverse reactions to transfusion. Walking past the ICU after work three days ago, he saw a room full of doctors and nurses giving an "ECMO" to a patient, his first meeting with the patient he is now caring for. Author | Zhongqingbao Zhongqingwang Trainee Reporter, Zhang Yi

Editor | Liu Shixin

It was almost a one in a million chance that Zhang Ning, a emergency physician at Wuhan First Hospital, and nine other college students would meet in the same city 15 years after graduation to race against a brand new virus.

For 15 years, Zhang Ning and his classmates were scattered across the country, each with a different trajectory, and even his classmates were silent for much of the time.

Twenty years ago, they were teenagers who had just entered the Fourth Military Medical University, now known as the Air Force Medical University, and Zhang Hua was their common name.

Now, they are the mainstay of Chinese medicine. They from Xi'an, Changchun, Nanjing, Xinjiang, and other top up, to take up sensory control, critical, supplies, emergency work of all kinds. To save lives and protect doctors, they're on the same team, but they're so different.

"Some of the students in Wuhan couldn't hold on. "

The attack of the new pneumonia virus caught the medical staff a bit off guard at first.

The E.R. takes the brunt of it. Early, unusual fever symptoms have been spread in the emergency medical circle in Wuhan. One of Zhang Ning's classmates, Fang Qing, was an attending physician in the Emergency Department of a hospital in Wuchang District. On January 2, the hospital sent more staff to the fever clinic and began training for medical staff.

On January 25, after receiving a letter of help from Wuhan No. 7 Hospital, Fang Qing took seven doctors and 15 nurses to a ward with 48 patients. Due to the shortage of manpower, in addition to a critical care, a suction doctor, to many physicians, surgeons, including cardiologist Shi Jinhu is Fang Qing's college classmates.

Fang Qing is ward director, the first task is to let the disorder of the medical process to restore order. Each patient specific to the day what to do, to check what indicators, to what extent, what drugs? Fang Qing has to keep an eye on them one by one.

The youngest nurse was only 23, and some were as tall as an oxygen tank, carrying two or three tanks of oxygen every four hours a day. A full state of oxygen tank has 200 Jin, 39-year-old Fang Qing also can not carry, can only a little rolling, from the door to the patient side.

At the height of the illness, seven critically ill patients were intubated and aspirated simultaneously. But we don't have enough equipment. We don't have enough oxygen.

Such a situation makes many doctors especially uncomfortable, originally doctors can use modern medical equipment to help patients tide over the difficulties, but the shortage of supplies, really powerless.

An ordinary hospital, the general dialysis equipment is only a few dozen, not more than a hundred. But in those first few days, demand was running into the thousands. "A sudden increase in the number of critically ill patients paralyzed the hospital, " Fang recalled.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
At 1:30 am on February 29, medical staff were wearing protective clothing in the buffer zone of Wuhan First Hospital. Lu Chong, a trainee reporter at the China Youth Daily

Unlike Fang's anxiety, Zhang Ning's classmate Xu Chaohui, who came from Xi'an to support him, worries that the wards of many ordinary hospitals do not meet the requirements of three zones and two channels for infectious diseases. The long-time infection control department doctor said that the house can not be torn down again, many of the new pneumonia designated hospitals zoning renovation than the new hospital is more difficult.

The Wuchang Hospital he supports is in trouble. Under normal circumstances, medical staff can take off their masks and eat and drink water in the clean area, but the original passageways and buffers of Wuchang Hospital are too close together. Stripping Room only three or four square meters, out of more doctors, some off to the last, some just started off, it is easy to cause cross-infection.

Wuchang Hospital spent two days reclassifying the Yellow Zone (buffer zone) and the red zone (exclusion zone) . The hospital's problems are not just structural, but the head of the hospital, Liu Zhiming, has been hit by an infection that has hit morale among the hospital's staff. The doctors who came to the aid had a common belief that they should go ahead and give their colleagues at the hospital a break.

Before setting out, Liu Ye, who had been working in Changchun after graduation, learned from his classmates in Wuhan that the front-line medical staff were about to give up.

When you can't keep a patient in the first place, it's really hard

Zhang Ning's classmate, Liu Ye, who had come from Changchun to help, was a doctor in the intensive care unit. His patient, Lao Li, was the first patient at Chi Yuan Hospital to use ECMO.

An ECMO is one hundred thousand, and it's very expensive, and it's not a treatment that's available in general medicine. ECMO was originally used to maintain vital signs in heart transplant patients. Now severe new coronary pneumonia eventually leads to heart and lung failure, so ECMO should be useful to doctors.

On his second day at Ecmo, Li's numbers were good. But then heart problems, although the blood oxygen up, the heart has been bad, or ultimately did not salvage. This caught the doctors off guard. "He took eight or nine days to get better, but he left so quickly. "

Li spent 13 days in the intensive care unit, which is not an easy thing, the doctors believe he can survive, and even imagined the scene of Li transferred to the General Ward, and finally discharged from the hospital.

Zhang Ning heard that two days after his death, Liu Ye received a call from his daughter, want to know the circumstances of his final departure.

That night, Liu Ye silently listened to the crying sound in the telephone. He told Lao Li's daughter that the old man had gone peacefully and that he had left in a coma and should feel no pain.

Lao Li's daughter said, thank you, thank you.

"You can't imagine how hard it was for me as a doctor when your father died. I managed your father for 13 days. I thought Lao Li would be a good example for me to manage, but I didn't think it would be like this after I went to ECMO, liu Ye also choked up.

Doctors occasionally communicate these frustrations. For a while, though the number of new patients dropped, there were a few who were getting sicker. Doctors often have to face, "the day watch this person also call me, the next night shift shift, the patient is not" , "the protective clothing is not off, the patient's heart stopped, without any signs, do not give him the opportunity" .

In the general course of the disease, after the disease will experience coma, heart, blood pressure index deterioration, is a slow process, but new coronary pneumonia is not. From a bad condition to rescue only half an hour or an hour, rescue before the patient also told the doctor has a chat, do not come to no.

If you witness a patient from birth to death, you will know a deep understanding of the dangers of the disease, rescue point where? What to do at what time in advance, and when he starts to slide, you need to reach out and pull him.

Despite their experience, doctors who come to their aid are sometimes unable to avoid despair. Liu Ye once told another chief doctor, "many patients are dying in my hands, and I can promise to do so. " But at that stage, watching the patients now taking over leave one by one, liu Ye felt his ability did not use, so many years of technology in the face of this disease seems to be unable to unfold.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In the early morning hours of February 29, nurses turned over a comatose new-onset coronary pneumonia patient in the isolation ward of the negative-pressure ICU at Wuhan First Hospital to avoid pressure sores from prolonged inactivity. By Li Qiang, China Youth Daily intern reporter

KEEP SAFE and celebrate the New Year

In addition to saving lives, doctors also have to take care of patients'psychology.

Long-term students living in Wuhan told the old students to come to support, the local people have a characteristic, axis. A 50-year-old aunt let Liu ye feel this "axis. ". She is Liu Ye admitted to the first batch of patients, at the beginning of the hospital conditions are not satisfied, at night still can hear the voice of the construction. As soon as we met, she threw the doctor a series of questions: When can I see my family? When will I be well? What kind of hospital is this? How did this happen? What can you give me?

"In the end or worried about the treatment is not guaranteed. " Explained a half-day to let the aunt to ease concerns. Liu Ye told this aunt, come to support each doctor in the local can act alone, some usually a hard to get, now specialized treatment, we do not worry. Now that you've had a good session, we're GONNA go through it step by step. Ninety-nine steps down, one more shiver to go.

The first thing a doctor has to do is give confidence to the patient. Fang Qing said that the previous task may be more to save lives, now both to improve the cure rate, but also to pay attention to patients'mood.

Not long ago, 48 patients at Wuhan No. 7 Hospital received a heartwarming breakfast of Millet Porridge cooked by nurses.

Originally, the virus infection will cause oral secondary infection, many patients suffering from angular stomatitis, cheilitis, ulcers, angular herpes, to the middle of the disease, can not eat lunch boxes, sore throat. A ward round, a nurse found that the patient week father silently shed tears, depressed. After inquiring only then knows, the patient intestines and stomach is not good, the appetite is bad, frequency nausea and vomiting. Father Zhou said, his isolation treatment, his family is not around, not accustomed to the hospital diet, would like to drink a bowl of hot porridge.

This ward is an old man with an average age of 65. "You think how comfortable it is to have hot porridge when you have a fever. " And there was a shortage of logistical resources. Fang Qing suggested to the head nurse that she cook some Millet Porridge in the ward so that they could drink it at any time. So, the person in charge of material distribution brought an electric rice cooker from home, plus the millet donated by caring people, so, hot porridge to the mouth of the patient. The patient was able to eat, so he got over it.

Because home infection, Ward there are five couples, are seventy mother in law father. On Valentine's Day, Fang Qing came up with an idea and prepared flowers for his father so they could be sent to his wife. "When I get out of the hospital, my wife will take you to Europe. We'll take a ferry from Shanghai to Japan to see the Cherry Blossoms, " one man said in a video

"The ward is isolated from the virus, not from love. " Two patients on the same birthday, doctors and nurses have sent cards, paintings, poems. Fang Qing wrote a sentence: keep safe, qingyu year.

For critically ill patients, intubation, breathing, entering the ICU is a frightening memory, if the patient's mind is not strong enough, even if discharged, will leave a great trauma in the heart. 'We want to make the ward less depressing, ' Fang said. 'disaster is always temporary, but people still have to live their whole lives. '.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In the early morning hours of February 29, a newly diagnosed pneumonia patient who had been intubated in the isolation ward of the negative pressure ICU at Wuhan First Hospital spent most of the day in a coma. To prevent the tube from pressing on the patient, the nurse blew a balloon with her glove and placed it next to the patient's pillow to prevent pressure sores. In order to adjust the atmosphere, the balloon painted a smiling face, writing "refueling" the word. China Youth Daily Trainee reporter Li Qiang

A lot of them made it back

The closest doctors to the danger also have a dike behind them, and Xu Zhaohui, who is in charge of infection control at the hospital, is one of their protectors.

From home back to the unit, and then to support Wuhan, less than 24 hours, he bounced around three places.

Xu Zhaohui was still in his hometown in Lujiang County, Anhui Province, on Jan. 24, five months after his father had an esophagectomy and he planned to spend the New Year at home with his parents. More than three o'clock in the morning, Xu Zhaohui received a call from the unit, Wuhan need support.

Years of infection control Xu Zhaohui heart understand that the infectious disease is very strong, there is a certain mortality. There has never been such a thing in the history as sealing off the city during the New Year.

He hung up and immediately booked a flight from Hefei to Xi'an. Although he can only see his son once a year, his 73-year-old father also supports it. "It's nice to have a son who can be used by the state for a long time. " Before he left, his father told him to protect himself, when you're doing something good for your country.

Xu Zhaohui is still on the plane, the other side, his wife in Xi'an has prepared his luggage, change clothes, daily necessities, Washbasin, finished driving to the airport to wait for him.

More than 11:00 noon to fly to Xi'an, did not have time to go home to see two children, Xu Zhaohui immediately with rucksack rushed to the unit.

That night, the unit for everyone to do a few dishes, prepared a rich dinner, the leadership in the dining hall to Xu Zhaohui and colleagues send off. His wife let him stay some stomach, she secretly came from home, with half a chicken, in Xu Zhaohui's single dormitory, two people also together to eat a meal.

At 11:58 pm, the medical team arrived in Wuhan on time. Empty Feeling, let Xu Zhaohui for a time did not return to mind, "the city really quiet down. ". But he did not particularly nervous, to the hotel, there are still service personnel reception, which means that at least order is stable. For a disease control worker, the ability of a place to function in an orderly fashion, and the ability of commands to land on the ground, means that the most critical task -- quarantine -- can be undertaken, and the situation can still be controlled.

As one of the first army doctors to support Wuhan, he remembers that "winning the war with zero infection" is a requirement of the leadership before the departure. Not only must we complete the rescue mission, but also our medical staff must take a lot of them back, both equally important.

Xu Zhaohui is in charge of the second half, and he wants to do a lot of work in the front. The first thing I did after coming to Wuhan was to train the medical staff of the Wuchang Hospital. Personal protection, he says, must be done in strict accordance with standard procedures, which are responsible for their own lives, as well as for the team. If you don't pass, you'll never get on the job. The use of protective clothing is not standard, on the repeated wearing off practice.

Gong Jiuyu, who works in a local hospital in Wuhan, heard that his old classmate Xu Chaohui had arrived and decided that he might have material difficulties and unaccustomed to eating, so he contacted him. Xu Zhaohui reply, eat OK. Gong Jiuyu was afraid he was polite, so he took the initiative to order takeout, sent a few boxes of yogurt, instant noodles top one.

But aside from the fact that he forgot to bring his razor charger, Xu did have no problems with supplies. "because everyone was wearing masks, no one knew how long my beard had grown. " When the second rescue team arrived, his co-worker also brought his charger.

In fact, the greatest difficulty is the lack of medical supplies. When they first arrived at the Wuchang Hospital, the protective screen to cover the SPLASHES was gone. They purchased a batch of transparent soft plastic tablecloths about 3 mm in size, cut them into pieces and punched out a dot. The back cover was threaded through with a rope, the place that forehead touches pastes soft foam soft glue, make face screen by oneself.

On the same day that Liu Ye arrived at the aid hospital, Xu Zhaohui also completed training for the renovation of Wuchang Hospital, guiding a hospital's construction supervision to ensure that every detail is correct: which faucets need to be non-contact, how to do the negative pressure transfer chamber, which angle to install UV disinfection lamp is the most accurate, how to deal with the medical waste generated. In addition, to ensure that the flow of people, goods and air flow forward, that is, into the contaminated area, can not be returned to the potential contaminated area, not to return to the clean area.

He should pay special attention to the medical staff fatigue to the extreme "iq drop" time, ready for emergency treatment box and detailed operating diagram, a need, to ensure that the first time to find emergency tools and methods. Precisely because of the sense control personnel's strict control, only then lets the direct contact patient's doctor have the strength to say, "as long as completes the three-level protection not to be afraid. "

At that time, responsible for critical, sensory control, supplies of the doctor students may be in a hospital, but no one knows from each other may be only a wall away.

It wasn't until mid-february that Liu Ye accidentally ran into Jin Xin, an old classmate he hadn't seen in 15 years, while receiving supplies. It turned out that almost at the same time as Liu Ye arrived, Jin Xin also followed a medical team of nearly 170 people from Nanjing, he was responsible for the medical support of the assisted hospital.

In his first week, Jin Xin could only sleep three or four hours a day. Today's supplies and medicines are used up, and if they are not in place the next day, medical work may have to be stopped. The supplies he needed, which often arrived at one or two o'clock in the morning, had to be unloaded at once and put into storage. The hospital has 1,000 beds, about 30 boxes of protective clothing arrive every day, 50 pieces a box, plus face masks, tens of thousands of items are quickly digested here, and a 10 ton oxygen tank can only guarantee a day's oxygen consumption for patients at the hospital, supplies are still tight.

Long time no see, Liu Ye does not even believe that Jin Xin has full head of white hair.

A bus carrying passengers passes on the second ring road in Wuchang District, Hubei Province, on the evening of February 18. China Youth Daily, China Youth Daily Reporter, Li Junhui

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Students who grow up eating rou Jia mo help "hot and dry noodles"

No one volunteered to come to Wuhan. Xu Zhaohui, for example, didn't know until a classmate saw the photo on the poster. When some assisted hospitals opened up medical information, there was a chance to run into students in the group of News, everyone's secret was broken, then a search found that there have been seven or eight people in Wuhan.

Most let Gong Jiuyu is surprised, oneself far in Urumqi's Bestie also came. In College, they were thick as thieves. Before coming, bestie asks her, what climate is Wuhan now, what dress should take?

The girls came from Xinjiang to support a hospital in Wuhan, and Gong said that Wuhan and Urumqi were even jet-lagged, and that she was grateful that they had traveled so far to join the fight.

Dr. Zhang Ning's circle of friends

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Zhang Ning, a native of Wuhan, is proud of his classmates. Several Times after graduation, he invited them to visit his hometown, but his work kept him so busy that no one ever came. They said, "the brothers and sisters who grew up eating Rou Jia mo together went to help 'hot and dry noodles' . "

Zhang Ning's classmates are among the more than 40,000 medical workers who have already arrived in Wuhan.

The Second Brigade where they went to school was the glorious Zhang Hua Brigade. In 1982, Zhang Hua, a 24 year old student at the Fourth Military Medical University, died trying to save an elderly man from drowning?

It had a huge impact on young people at the time, Zhang Ning said. The first lesson for the class of grade 2,000 is about Zhang Hua's education: Stand up when you're in trouble.

Almost every second division division has its share of glory, including the subsequent Mount Hua Rescue. "They held hands and stood on the edge of the cliff to block the people who fell from above, " Ms. Gong recalled. "If one of them let go, everyone collapsed. "

The Second Brigade five years a session, the last graduation of the senior to the next class just entered the class monitor, words and example, like a baton, will pass down the honor with action. But being a role model is more than just a title. It also means more responsibility. The group was more demanding, more disciplined. Over the next five years, they forged a deeper bond through their experiences of hardship and training.

A student of the Department of ultrasound also came to Wuhan at the end of January. Previously, he had been approved, in March this year from the army transfer, independent job selection. And yet, here he is. In their minds, it's a time to honor the elders.

Twenty years later, these teenagers have become a mainstay of Chinese doctors. Some have been department heads, some have become university doctoral directors, some have participated in the Wenchuan County earthquake relief, some have gone to aid the Zaire Ebolavirus. When they received the mission, they did not hesitate to say, "duty calls, " "we do not go on who, " "we can go on. ".

On the afternoon of March 7, several new coronary pneumonia patients walked out of the hospital and were ready to transfer to the Raytheon Mountain Hospital. On the same day morning, 25 people were discharged from the square-cabin hospital in the living room of Wuhan, and 59 people were transferred to the Leishenshan Hospital in the afternoon. With the last patient transferred out, Wuhan Living Room Shelter Hospital Patients "zero. ". China Youth Daily, China Youth Daily, Zhao di / photo

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Students Group to the North and south of them again linked together. In the group, it's all about the epidemic. They share up-to-date information and data and share expertise with each other. Let's discuss the situation of new drug research and development. The person of Clinical first-line does not have time to check data, the classmate of the rear actively helps to find a document. "It's not just our classmates, but maybe all the doctors in the country, " Liu said. I hope there will be good news soon.

In fact, Liu Ye had good news in Wuhan. On February 21, Liu Ye spent a special 38th birthday on the frontline of the war epidemic, the day he was sworn in as a member of the Communist Party.

Liu Ye, who is still unmarried, may be the only one among his classmates. The students described the boy as handsome, humorous and sunny. But in Liu Ye's own eyes, in the life he has not had the soldier that kind of "board Zheng" .

The Party members are in his mind "high and mighty" . After graduation, he always felt he was a little behind. "there is a gap, do not give party members drag behind" , holding this idea, Liu Ye slowly became the yard "headache" single age did not join the party young men.

Before setting out from Changchun, Liu Ye gave the director of the medical office an application for joining the party. Handed over secretly told himself, finally can apply to join the party. During his time in Wuhan, he also sent his field diary to the Party organization.

It was a complete coincidence that no one at the swearing-in ceremony mentioned his birthday. More than 7 pm, the hotel sent a bowl of noodles, a root in the end of the long-lived noodles, Liu ye all eat, a little soup base is not left, feel very warm.

Two years ago this spring, Liu Ye climbed to the top of Snake Mountain and stood at the top of Yellow Crane Tower overlooking the Yangtze River Bridge. Coming back to Wuhan is like going to war. In his resolution, Liu wrote 16 words: Use me in the first battle, use me to win, Walk the Line.
